      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the sponge",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C conventional (160°C fan) and line a 12-hole muffin tin with paper cases. Sift the flour, cocoa, bicarbonate of soda, baking powder, and salt into a bowl. In a separate large bowl, beat the softened butter and caster sugar together for 3 to 4 minutes until pale and fluffy. Beat in the eggs one at a time. Mix the buttermilk, red gel colouring, vinegar, and vanilla together, then add alternately with the flour mixture, beginning and ending with flour. Fold with a spatula, do not overbeat. The batter will be a vivid crimson.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide the batter evenly among the cases, filling each about two-thirds full. Bake for 18 to 22 minutes until the tops spring back when pressed gently and a skewer through the centre comes out clean. Cool in the tin for 5 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack and cool completely before frosting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Frost",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the cream cheese and softened butter together until smooth and lump-free. Add the sifted icing sugar and vanilla and beat until fluffy, 3 minutes on medium. The frosting should be thick enough to pipe. Use a palette knife for swirls or a piping bag fitted with a round or star tip. The ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "cupcake-frosting",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "techniqueLink",
                "attrs": {
                  "label": "cupcake-frosting",
                  "techniqueSlug": "cupcake-frosting"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " technique for swirling applies; pipe from the outside edge inward, building up to a peak.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
